    "creditline": "Gift of Philippe Apeloig",
    "description": "Staggered, smeared black letters on light blue ground read \"bruits du monde.\" The letters are rotated in different directions. \"F\u00eate du livre\" (book festival) is printed in smaller white text above the word \"monde.\"",
    "justification": "Philippe Apeloig designed Bruits du Monde (Noises of the World) for an annual French book fair that takes place in Aix-en-Provence.  For this poster, Apeloig created a font resembling strokes of charcoal or some other soft substance that appears to have been vandalized by smearing or rubbing out the type.  Such a masterful typographic distortion suggests the conflict of many individual writers who are searching to express their individual voices or the millions of tears shed globally in all the books published annually.",
